{"abstract": "Legacy is about to introduce a new antismoking effort, which takes a decidedly less rebellious tone than its previous \u201cTruth\u201d campaign.", "web_url": "https://www.nytimes.com/2014/08/11/business/a-less-defiant-tack-in-a-campaign-to-curb-smoking-by-teenagers-.html", "snippet": "Legacy is about to introduce a new antismoking effort, which takes a decidedly less rebellious tone than its previous \u201cTruth\u201d campaign.", "lead_paragraph": "SMOKING had long been a hallmark of teenage rebellion when \u201cTruth,\u201d a campaign from Legacy, introduced its first antismoking commercial in 2000. In the commercial, young people gather at the New York headquarters of the Philip Morris tobacco company and dump 1,200 body bags, representing the number of daily deaths attributed to smoking. The spot sought to shift a perception of cigarettes as a symbol of rebellion to one of the tobacco industry as the real enemy to rebel against. ", "print_section": "B", "print_page": "5", "source": "The New York Times", "multimedia": [{"rank": 0, "subtype": "xlarge", "caption": null, "credit": null, "type": "image", "url": "images/2014/08/11/business/11Adco/11Adco-articleLarge.jpg", "height": 339, "width": 600, "subType": "xlarge", "crop_name": "articleLarge", "legacy": {"xlarge": "images/2014/08/11/business/11Adco/11Adco-articleLarge.jpg", "xlargewidth": 600, "xlargeheight": 339}}, {"rank": 0, "subtype": "jumbo", "caption": null, "credit": null, "type": "image", "url": "images/2014/08/11/business/11Adco/11Adco-jumbo.jpg", "height": 579, "width": 1024, "subType": "jumbo", "crop_name": "jumbo", "legacy": {}}, {"rank": 0, "subtype": "superJumbo", "caption": null, "credit": null, "type": "image", "url": "images/2014/08/11/business/11Adco/11Adco-superJumbo.jpg", "height": 711, "width": 1257, "subType": "superJumbo", "crop_name": "superJumbo", "legacy": {}}, {"rank": 0, "subtype": "thumbnail", "caption": null, "credit": null, "type": "image", "url": "images/2014/08/11/b